POST MARKET REPORT 20 Sep 2023  #Nifty opened gap down, majorily because of negative news from #HDFCBank 2024 guidance.  Nomura downgraded HDFCBank's target saying that 2024 revenue and NIM will be impacted negatively, as asset quality will be hit due to high costs.  #Reliance and #HDFCBank together contributed to 150 points fall in #Nifty. Once both started falling, other heavyweight stocks, #smallcap and #midcap also started falling.  The US 10-year yield rising was also a concern for today's market fall.  P.S #HDFCBank looks in a very good valuation compared to its peers. However, it might take time to go up, once all the headwinds are over. Not a recommendation to buy
